❤️‍🔥💕 Imagine if…💕❤️‍🔥

You got everything you’ve ever dreamt of ☺️ 

Your dream career or job, an amazing relationship, all the world goodies you can imagine. 

This is my daily morning routine: imagining what I want, getting very excited about it. 

You should try it. And then go after what you want 💕

💕 Standards ❤️‍🔥

As many of you may know, I’m part of a badass business network called Apex 💯 

Within this network, we are constantly reminded of our standards. Core Values. We do the work. F*ck Your Excuses and many more. 

Successful people will always get ahead of everyone else. It’s their habits. Simple, basic habits. 

💯 They arrive early and leave late 

💯 Do more of them than what is asked. Poor mindset people are often heard saying, ”well I’m not getting paid for that so I’m not doing it” 

💯 They push in their chairs, they put the shopping cart back, they pick up garbage, they take out the trash. They do these things without being asked to do it. 

💯 Take responsibility. Poor mindset is often heard saying, “nobody told me, I didn’t know, it’s not my fault, etc”. Successful people are the opposite. “Let me figure this out, I’ll do it, I’ll look after it, I can handle this, I’ll follow up, etc.”

When you constantly blame the world, and it’s never you, you can’t expand. 

On a daily basis, I’m taking an online class or reading a book. Marketing, accounting, business development, psychology, strategy. 

Daily calls with business people include the same conversations. 

How you do one thing is how you do everything. 

Standards. Small, tiny habits turn into huge successes.

I ❤️‍🔥 my girlfriends! 💯💕 They are the most beautiful girls in Vegas. They are smart, wise, business owners and I’m so proud of each one of them. 

They inspire me to always do better, work hard, make a difference. They understand when I cancel or don’t show up, yet I always get the invite. 

My little world is a better place because of them. I love every single one of you 💕❤️‍🔥

Beauty & Brains 💕 Work ethic ❤️‍🔥 Values 💯 

Here’s the winning formula for success, a theme that we all have in common. 

Drop any one of these ladies at the lowest level position in any company, and I can guarantee you they will climb all the way to the top in any company or business. 

Here’s the secret formula to accomplish the same in any place you work:

💯 always arrive early and leave late (almost every single successful person does this)

💯 do more than what is asked of you (even simple things like picking up the garbage, pushing in chairs, wiping a counter) 

💯 take responsibility for your own actions and actions of others. Example:

Stephanie here saw someone else’s employee at someone else’s businesses sit there and do nothing while the other movers moved furniture. In her stilettos she got up and helped the movers get the job accomplished. 

Results: she establishes herself as someone you can trust with your business, someone who takes action and someone that can THINK for themselves and others.

💯 have you ever seen any of these ladies, standing around with their heads down, scrolling through their phones?! 🤣 Never, ever!! Their heads are up, always looking for something to do, an action to take, to make a contribution.

The more you do without being asked, the more you end up getting in life. Leave the space where you go in a better condition than when you find it. 

Give more, get more. Successful people are always giving. Give first and success will follow. 💕❤️‍🔥

Life is full of unexpected twists and turns. 

We often find ourselves feeling overwhelmed or helpless, but it's important to remember that these feelings are only temporary. Life isn't always easy, but when we're faced with obstacles and adversity, it's how we choose to respond that matters most. 

It's okay to feel down sometimes; it is a normal human emotion in the face of difficulty. The key is not to stay down for too long, but rather to use those moments as an opportunity for growth and resilience. 

Remember: no storm lasts forever! If you can keep your head up and keep pushing forward, you'll eventually find your way out of whatever darkness you are facing. 

So keep your chin up - because you have all the strength and courage within yourself to get through life’s ups and downs!

Life is short - why not make the most of it? We all work hard, but sometimes we forget to play and have fun too. Adventure doesn't have to be big, scary or dangerous; it can be found in the everyday as well. If you want to get the most out of life, you need to start living with an adventurous spirit!

Adventure doesn't always mean daring feats like skydiving or scaling mountains, it can be as simple as trying something new or taking the time to explore what's right in front of us. Whether it's a spontaneous road trip or exploring a city you've never been to before, when we open ourselves up to new experiences, they become more than just memories - they enrich our lives and make us feel alive! So don't let fear get in the way of adventure; embrace each moment and venture forth into unknown territory. 

Remember, life is about having fun and seizing opportunities for growth and exploration. Don’t let another day pass without going out there, getting lost and finding yourself again! Live your life with an enthusiastic thirst for adventure - because anything is possible when you take chances, follow your heart and enjoy every ride along the way!

“The purpose of life is not happiness, but adventure. 

💕 To live is to explore and discover, to take risks and push your boundaries—to take the road less travelled and make your own path.” 

💯 – Jordan Pedersen

Some people are so broken that they come without a drain plug 💔 

It’s completely irrelevant what kind of oil (love) you pour into them. You give them unlimited love, time, attention, support & patience. 

But if they don’t have a drain plug, all of that effort just pours right out. It will not work, it can’t work. It’s not the oil, it’s the drain plug. It’s not even broken, they just don’t have it. 

So you can’t force it, can’t pray about it, can’t manifest it. It’s really sad to see too, cuz the machine itself is so beautiful and has so much potential. So much what could have been…

But there’s no drain plug…so stop wasting that high grade oil and time of pouring it in cuz it will never be…

Life is not Sunshine & Rainbows ❤️‍🩹 

I know, we’re to post only positive things but let’s get real, there are times that just suck. 

For some of us, if not many of us, we’re going through a seasonal depression. The weather is bleh: grey, cool, sort of raining, the palm trees blowing in the wind. 

I have lots of time but no money season. Time to go to gym and yet I lay on the couch. Emails piling up, plenty of time to do them and yet, screw it. Don’t wanna do it. 

Many people go through this about once a year. During the winter season. And like every other time, this season passes. 

Can’t give you ideas on how to get out of it, if I did, I’d use it myself. 

So, hunker down, stay in and know you’re not alone. As the seasons change, this too shall pass but just know, you’re not alone. 💕❤️‍🔥

I took an Uber the other day, a gentle reminder of how the 90% of the population think…

The lady blamed the economy for her lack of success. Wasn’t her fault, real estate is slow. She’s a licensed realtor but driving Uber to make ends meet until the market picks up again. 

We had something in common: we both work 7 days a week! 

Her reaction was, “ugh, it’s so awful!” Mine was, “well, I love my job so much I want to work daily and I’m blessed and excited to do so.” 

So complained about not making enough, jobs are so hard to come by these days 🧐 

I gave her my card and asked her to contact me, I’ll help her make more money. She gave me hers, realtor on one side, travel agent on the other side. 

She never did call… “jobs are so hard to come by…” and yet when it was offered, she did nothing. 

And this is 90% of the population. They blame others, they take no action, they make excuses. 

It’s easier than ever to be successful right now, 90% is too lazy to do anything.

“Why don’t you drink?” 🧐 

I watch and listen to people when they do drink, you learn a lot about them. I don’t need to ask questions, I see it and hear it. 

The closet alcoholics: they, and only them alone, think they don’t have a drinking problem and yet they can barely go a full 24 or 48 hours without a drink.  That makes you an alcoholic 🤷🏻‍♀️ 

“You just don’t know how to have fun” 🤨 

If you only know how to have fun with alcohol, perhaps it’s time to have a chat with the man in the mirror. I operate on fuel/adrenaline, not booze. 

They often smell like booze, they slur their words and think no one knows…we all know. 

Although you may think you’re the fun one in the group, the life of the party, I see it as a sign of weakness. You have no control over yourself and yet when there are consequences to actions because you were drinking, it’s “not your fault” 

You are weak, lost control over yourself, numbing the pain of something else and disguising yourself as the life of the party. 

Why don’t I drink? 🍸

I like to be in control of myself, alcohol ruins my body, it’s an unnecessary expense and instead of being the life of the party, I enjoy being the dependable one instead 💕
